  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Impact of unilateral modulation of deep brain stimulation of the subthalamic nucleus on
      freezing of gait in Parkinson's disease
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Unilateral modulation of subthalamic stimulation and its impact on freezing of gait in
      Parkinson's disease will be studied.

      In a cross-over, doubleblind, randomized study, a 30% reduction of stimulation intensity of
      the less impacted side will be compared with chronic treatment with regard to frequency and
      duration of freezing of gait episodes.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
